1. According to Drucker, why are people critical to organizational change management?
solution : B. People ultimately control how hard and how well they work

2. Which of the following best describes a key element of the Bridges model?
solution : A. External changes require people to make internal transitions

3. In Kotter's Eight Steps process for organizational change, what is a good way to overcome complacency and get people moving?
solution : C. Paint a picture of a major opportunity or a looming crisis
